	<!-- Mission Statement -->
	<h2>Mission</h2>
	<p>
		I'm a <strong>Product Architect</strong> (Solution Architect / Application Architect) with over 
		<strong>18 years of experience</strong> designing and delivering enterprise software. My mission is 
		to transition engineering teams from <em>"Master Blacksmiths"</em> — relying on manual, effort-based 
		labor — to <em>"Master Goldsmiths"</em>, where high-precision logic handles business uncertainty 
		while humans focus on what matters most.
	</p>

	<!-- What I Do -->
	<h2>What I Do</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Review & migrate</strong> existing service architectures toward composable target states</li>
		<li><strong>Design architecture</strong> for new features within legacy products</li>
		<li><strong>Architect greenfield products</strong> from first principles</li>
		<li><strong>Refine reference architectures</strong> that teams can build upon with confidence</li>
	</ul>

	<!-- The "Lego" Framework -->
	<h2>The "Lego" Framework</h2>
	<p>
		My architectural philosophy is built around composability and repairability:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Standardized Skeleton</strong> — Foundations follow company-proven patterns (.NET, REST, SQL) with 
		immutable interfaces defined through Spec-Driven Development (SDD).</li>
		<li><strong>Lego Slices</strong> — Features are built as independent, parallel-safe modules. As long as they 
		fit the standardized "joints" (contracts), teams develop in parallel without falling into the Waterfall trap.</li>
		<li><strong>Repairable Anatomy</strong> — Components are modular enough to be replaced or repaired 
		without compromising the core skeleton — designed for "plastic surgery."</li>
	</ul>

	<!-- Architecture Convictions -->
	<h2>Architecture Convictions</h2>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Hexagonal Architecture</strong> with Ports & Adapters for complex domain APIs, aided by CQRS and DDD — 
		but always valuing simplicity over complexity.</li>
		<li><strong>Hybrid Microservices</strong> using DDD, CQRS, and design-first/spec-first approaches with 
		strong schema management and observability tooling.</li>
		<li><strong>SOLID + CUPID principles</strong>, with deep experience in MACH and PBC (Packaged Business Capabilities) 
		architectures and COTS applications.</li>
		<li><strong>Ideal API topology</strong>: GraphQL for UI-facing APIs, gRPC with Protobuf for internal services, 
		Kafka for async messaging, REST for external integrations.</li>
		<li>I adapt this ideal architecture <strong>pragmatically within enterprise constraints</strong>.</li>
	</ul>

	<!-- AI Philosophy -->
	<h2>AI Philosophy</h2>
	<p>
		AI is the <strong>"Great Teacher"</strong> and the engine for the structural 90% of software engineering tasks. 
		Human value is found in the final 10% — refinement, creative problem-solving, and business alignment. 
		I actively practice AI-Augmented Software Engineering using agentic AI tools to accelerate 
		architectural workflows.
	</p>

